name: Mimit

techniques.name: DNA Extraction
techniques.description: The needle-prick doesn't inflict much damage, but Mimit uses the DNA sample to adapt its defense, bestowing SPD .
techniques.effectText: DNA Extraction deals damage to a single other target and gifts the user with SPD .

trivia: Mimit is the only Temtem that needs to have a quest completed before it can be found in the wild.
Mimit has a sticker on the official Temtem Discord, beating Chromeon by 66 votes, out of the total 274 votes, in the 2nd sticker poll.
Mimit has 2 emotes on the official Temtem Discord.
Mimit was first teased in a 2020 Halloween Twitter post.
gameDescription: Mimit has the honor of being the very first Digital ever created. The genomic reservoir contained in its tail allows it an unequalled ability to replicate any other Temtem species, making it the ultimate breeder.

trivia: Oree is the starter Temtem for the player’s rival, Max.
Oree is mentioned in The creation of Digital Temtem.
Oree is 1 of only 6 temtem with a sticker on the official Temtem Discord that didn't have to go through a sticker poll.
gameDescription: One of the first prototypes created in Nanto Labs, Oree's early versions were the forerunners of Digital Temtem. Inquisitive creatures by design, they show great curiosity and a boundless appetite for information.

trivia: Platimous is a Breeder Tier Temtem by PokéNinja, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. It was drawn by 50 Shades of Heliolisk. Crema and PokéNinja obtained the rights to add Platypet, Platox and Platimous to the game.

gameDescription: Charles Temwin described them as "Platox, but more so". This is usually taken as classic Arburian understatement: Platimous were amongst the most successful apex predators before large-scale taming, and remain very effective fighters.

trivia: Tateru was first revealed on Twitter.

Tateru has 5 emotes on the official Temtem Discord.

techniques.name: Madness Buff

techniques.name: Base Jump

techniques.effectText: Base Jump deals damage to a single other target.

gameDescription: Temtemologists believe Magmut developed their characteristic flaming mane as an adaptation to the colder and wetter climate of the Lochburg moors.

name: Paharo

techniques.name: Wind Blade
techniques.description: Lashing gales, like the frozen tramontane wind howling over the Loch.

techniques.name: Wind Burst
techniques.description: A terrifying gust of wind, capable of throwing a small airship off course.
techniques.effectText: Wind Burst deals damage to a single target.

trivia: Ampling was originally unnamed #32 on a list of scrapped Temtem that was to be voted to bring back on Kickstarter Update #2.

Ampling was the winner of the Chose a Temtem backer mini-game. Its name was proposed by a community member (ItsTomas) in the Official Discord, and later chosen as the winner during the Choose a Temtem names poll in the 6th update of Temtem's Kickstarter.

trivia: Orphyll was one of the scrapped Temtem designs that had a chance to be added into the game during the first "Choose a Temtem" mini-game. However, it was not selected in the end.

techniques.effectText: Misogi cures/removes all Status Conditions gifted/given/inflicted on the user.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also gifts the user with the Immune Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Magma Cannon
techniques.description: Like a surge of Anak lava to the face! Fire technique that burns for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Magma Cannon deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Burned Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Look out
techniques.description: This Temtem has (metaphorical) eyes on the back of its head. This hyperalert state makes it alerted for 5 turns and removes the Asleep status condition.
techniques.effectText: Look out gifts a single target with the Alerted Condition for 5 turns and cures them of the Asleep Condition. Unlike other techniques, it will set the duration of any previously gifted Alerted Conditions to 5 turns.

techniques.name: Quetza-leño
techniques.description: A party trick someone showed you once, involving a Fire Temtem, a log, and a bottle of Quetzaleño Reposado...
techniques.effectText: Quetza-leño deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its damage increases to 115 and priority increases to High.

techniques.name: Horror
techniques.description: Unspeakable nightmares! Obviously, they can only hurt an asleep target, but they do massive damage to the sleeper.
techniques.effectText: Horror deals damage to a single target if they're afflicted with the Asleep Condition.

techniques.name: Hallucination
techniques.description: Suggestive and Toxic visions that exhaust the mind and tire and trap the target for 2 turns.Used in combination with a Mental ally, the Hallucination does Special damage.
techniques.effectText: Hallucination inflicts a single other target with the Exhausted Condition and the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Mental ally, its class becomes Special with 100 damage.

techniques.name: Matter Teleport
techniques.description: Feels like being disintegrated into molecules - not nice. This Mental technique inflicts heavy damage.
techniques.effectText: Matter Teleport deals damage to a single target.

gameDescription: Fast and sinuous like wildfire, Aohi are cunning and sly creatures who routinely outsmart all but the most seasoned of tamers. Even in the wild, they delight in tricking the more gullible Reval.

techniques.synergyText: Due to the low damage and high priority, its most encouraged use is to damage allies with the Asleep Condition in order to wake them.

techniques.name: Bubbles
techniques.description: Bubbles! <3 This weakens the target by means of extreme cuteness.
techniques.effectText: Bubbles deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.description: An extreme version of the ice water bucket challenge that does real damage.
techniques.effectText: Ice Cubes deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, its STA Cost decreases to 9.

techniques.name: Revitalize
techniques.description: Antiseptic and a couple of bandages. Target recovers 20% HP.Antibiotics and a proper bandage. Target recovers 20% HP and Temtem 10%.

techniques.synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, its STA Cost decreases to 15 and also restores 10% of the user's maximum HP.

techniques.name: Toxic Slime
techniques.description: This takes the form of a repulsive wave of slime that hurts the body... and your self-esteem.
techniques.effectText: Toxic Slime deals damage to a single target.

trivia: Bigu is one of two Temtem that can not be found in the wild while its evolution can. The other is Smolzy.
gameDescription: If there's an easily underestimated Temtem, that's Bigu. Comically ill-tempered, many tamers have found to their cost that these gastropods compensate their slow pace with outstanding tenacity in battle.

gameDescription: These Temtem are flamboyant creatures with a funky sense of humor and boundless love for pranks and practical jokes. Many a naughty kid has donned a Babawa costume to cause havoc in the Quetzal Carnival.

name: 0b1

techniques.name: DC Beam
techniques.description: Lightning, an elemental force; not extremely powerful, but always reliable.
techniques.effectText: DC Beam deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Plasma Beam
techniques.description: A jet of superheated matter, right where it hurts. This technique does slight damage and burns a target for 1 turn.
techniques.effectText: Plasma Beam deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Burned Condition for 1 turn.

techniques.name: Nimble
techniques.description: Through rigorous training, Temtem can become extra fast and gain SPD .
techniques.effectText: Nimble gifts a single other target with SPD .

techniques.name: Chain Lightning
techniques.description: This miracle of Electric manipulation bounces 3 times clockwise for as long as it deals damage, dealing decreasing damage with each hit.
techniques.effectText: Chain Lightning deals damage to a single target then two other combatants in clockwise order from the initial target. The initial target takes 100% of the damage, the second takes 70%, and the third takes 60%. The chain of damage will fail to continue to the next target if the damage was blocked by the current target. Damage can be blocked if the target who would have taken damage has the Evading Condition, has the Electric Synthesize Trait, or, if the target is an ally, has the Friendship Trait.

techniques.name: Digithreat
techniques.description: Just like trash-posting, this technique is a slow way of inflicting damage to the mind...All those trash-posts are messing with your head... Used in combination with a Mental ally. Digithreat dooms the target for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Digithreat deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Mental ally, it also inflicts a 3 turn countdown of the Doomed Condition.

techniques.name: Electromagnetism
techniques.description: Electromagnetically bound, attacker and target are trapped for 3 turns, while target gets SPD .
techniques.effectText: Electromagnetism inflicts a single other target and the user with the Trapped Condition for 3 turns and inflicts the target with SPD .

techniques.name: Double Edge
techniques.description: Cuts both ways, in true Neutral fashion - inflicts moderate damage to the target, but also gives it DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Double Edge deals damage to a single other target and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its damage decreases to 1.

techniques.name: Data Corruption
techniques.description: Hacking your opponent's database takes some time, but it's worth it. This technique weakens SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Data Corruption inflicts a single other target with SPDEF .

techniques.name: Harmful Microwaves
techniques.description: Make your enemies feel like reheated coffee does! This technique inflicts moderate damage.
techniques.effectText: Harmful Microwaves deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Digital ally, its STA Cost decreases to 14 and priority increases to High.

techniques.name: Burrow
techniques.description: "In a hole in the ground there lived a Temtem..." which allowed it to evade for 4 turns.
techniques.effectText: Burrow gifts the user with the Evading Condition for 4 turns.

techniques.name: Bush
techniques.description: When in doubt, run and shout! This fast Nature technique helps your Temtem regenerate and evade for 1 turn.No more beating around the bush! Used in combination with a Earth ally, this technique gives SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Bush gifts the user with the Regenerated Condition and Evading Condition for 1 turn.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, it also gifts the user with SPDEF .

techniques.name: Sparks
techniques.description: Nothing perks you up like a spark-up! SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Sparks gifts a single target with SPATK .

techniques.name: Tesla Prison
techniques.description: An electromagnetic trap that does light damage and slows down the target: SPD .
techniques.effectText: Tesla Prison deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with SPD .

trivia:
0b1 and its evolution are the only two Temtem to have numbers in their species name.
Due to the restrictions on using numbers in Temtem nicknames, this means that they are also the only two Temtem that cannot be reverted to their original species name once they are given a nickname.

gameDescription: 0b1's simple and friendly appearance belies their boldness as a creation - they are the Digital embodiment of a subatomic particle, whose very existence raises almost as many questions as it answers for physics modeling.

techniques.effectText: Gaia restores 20% of the user's maximum HP and 100% of their maximum STA. The user will still overexert if they lack the required STA before use.

techniques.name: Sanative Rain

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 20% of allies maximum HP Restore 10% of rival's maximum HP

techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its priority increases to Normal and instead restores 20% of allies maximum HP and restores 10% of rival's maximum HP.

trivia: Saku was first revealed via Twitter.
Saku has 4 emotes on the official Temtem Discord.

The Temtem Discord community created "cults" worshipping Saku and Pigepic. The official Twitter account for Temtem later created a tweet pitting the “Sakult” and “Team Porket” against each other. The Sakult is currently the winner.

trivia: The concept and name of Owlhe was predicted in 2019 by dev Shuni#7105 (years before he started working at Crema Games) and Discord mod Lord Berial#8479, almost 3 years before it was revealed and introduced in the game. To this day it is unknown if Crema Games already had this idea or took it because it seemed good.
Owlhe is one of four Temtem that change one of the types their pre-evolved form has upon evolving. In this case, swapping Mental for Wind. The others are Barnshe, Loatle, and Waspeen.

trivia: The first Luma Barnshe was caught by Laknightress (IGN) during Alpha 1, with a 5% encounter rate and 1/4000 Luma chance.
Barnshe was first revealed via Twitter.
Barnshe is one of four Temtem that change one of the types their pre-evolved form has upon evolving. In this case, swapping Melee for Wind. The others are Owlhe, Loatle, and Waspeen.

As a result of Barnshe being a single-stage evolution before the introduction of Towly in Early Access 0.8, It was possible to obtain Barnshe eggs by breeding. This makes Barnshe the only evolved Temtem that is possible to be hatched directly from an egg.

trivia: An untamed Occlura can be seen in the overworld in the Mines of Mictlan, despite not being encountered there.

Occlura has a sticker on the official Temtem Discord, beating 14 other Temetem by only 5 votes, out of the total 331 votes, in the 10th sticker poll.
This was a special sticker poll with Temtem chosen by the Discord's Moderators.
This was a special sticker poll with Temtem chosen by the Discord's Moderators.
gameDescription: Despite its creepy appearance, Occlura are mineral-eaters that never pose any danger to humans. Their tame nature and their appetite for raw rock make them valuable assets for mining purposes, as the Tucmani know very well.

name: Myx

gameDescription: The oldest written records in Tucma indicate religious awe of Myx, considered to be embodiments of the "dark spirits". Some were considered to be celestial emissaries of Highabove, some evil messengers of Downbelow... but all were feared. With good reason.

techniques.effectText: Thunder Strike deals damage to a single target but inflicts the user with the Exhausted Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.effectText: Fiery Heist inflicts a single other target with the Seized Condition and the Burned Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Fire Tornado
techniques.description: Unleash a mighty Fire storm against your opponents. Try not to wear anything flammable...

techniques.name: Electric Storm
techniques.description: True Electric storm like the monsoon over Cipanku. Damages whole team.

techniques.synergyText: If used with a Fire ally, its damage increases to 90 and also inflicts the Burned Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Magma Cannon

techniques.name: Drought

techniques.effectText: Drought inflicts all other combatants on the battlefield with the Exhausted Condition and the Seized Condition for 2 turns but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Untangle
techniques.description: With a few swift movement, this techniques Untraps the target from any tangle. If trapped is removed successfully, the target gets DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Untangle cures a single target of the Trapped Condition and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF if they were cured from the Trapped Condition.

techniques.name: Shelter
techniques.description: Take cover! This slow technique gives DEF and SPDEF at the expense of leaving you Overexerted on the next turn.
techniques.effectText: Shelter gifts the user with DEF and SPDEF but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Toughen
techniques.description: When the going gets tough, the tough get going - and DEF !
techniques.effectText: Toughen gifts the user with DEF .

gameDescription: Initially mistaken as a minor mutation of Scarawatt, Scaravolt is strongly associated with Miyako and the bonfires the yamabushi would light on the mountaintops on cold nights. On such an occasion, a sighting of this Temtem was considered a good omen.

trivia: Saipat first appeared as small pieces of an image that were slowly revealed in the official Temtem Discord, until fans guessed its design while creating fan art.
Purple paint is traditionally made from the discarded shells of growing Saipat. They are carefully collected from where the young adult Saipat discard them, then crushed into a fine powder.
Saipat has an emote on the official Temtem Discord.
gameDescription: Nothing says 'amateur' like making fun of Saipat. Sure, they might look comical at first sight, but nobody who has faced a totally focused Saipat, sturdy coral sai in hand, takes them anything but seriously.

techniques.name: Burrow

techniques.name: Brace

techniques.name: Drought
techniques.description: A bone-dry technique that leaves every Temtem on the battlefield except the user Exhausted and Seized for 2 turns, and the attacker overextended next turn.
techniques.effectText: Drought inflicts all other combatants on the battlefield with the Exhausted Condition and the Seized Condition for 2 turns but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Untangle

techniques.name: Mud Shower

techniques.effectText: Mud Shower deals damage to a single target.

gameDescription: Bubbly and cheerful, this Temtem is the protagonist of an animation series aimed at warning children of the dangers of fire. It has been a lifelong friend to many first-time tamers.

techniques.description: An accurate strike at the target's main pressure point, ignoring its defenses to deal exactly 100 damage without waking it up.
techniques.effectText: Dim Mak deals an exact 100 damage to a single other target, regardless of DEF, SPDEF, Type Effectivness or Traits. It will also not cause a target afflicted with the Asleep Condition to wake up.

techniques.name: Inner Spirit
techniques.description: It is said this technique channels the spirit of a long-lost, draconic variety of Temtem, for massive damage.
techniques.effectText: Inner Spirit deals damage to a single target.

techniques.name: Execution
techniques.description: "Omnes vulnerant, postuma necat". Slowly the hour creeps onwards... it does only slight damage, but if that leaves the Temtem under 35% of their total HP... it's over for them.
techniques.effectText: Execution deals damage to a single other target and if this damage would put them below 35% of their maximum HP, they're instead instantly knocked-out.

techniques.name: Soul Shout
techniques.description: A mighty scream, powered by the Temtem's very soul, inflicting considerable damage on an enemy.
techniques.effectText: Soul Shout deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Misogi
techniques.description: The monks of Miyako developed this technique to eliminate all altered states on the Temtem.Using this waterfall meditation with a Water ally, you become immune for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Misogi cures/removes all Status Conditions gifted/given/inflicted on the user.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also gifts the user with the Immune Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Double Edge
techniques.description: Cuts both ways, in true Neutral fashion - inflicts moderate damage to the target, but also gives it DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Double Edge deals damage to a single other target and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its damage decreases to 1.

techniques.name: Zen Meditation
techniques.description: Focus on your breathing. Remember, no effort, no resistance... The technique consumes 0 Stamina and boosts your ATK and SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Zen Meditation gifts the user with ATK and SPATK .

techniques.name: Sanative Rain

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 20% of allies maximum HP Restore 10% of rival's maximum HP

techniques.description: Known as "the blessing rains of Kisiwa", this shamanic technique heals 15% of every Temtem on the battlefield..Used in combination with a Wind ally, Sanative Rain heals allied Temtem by 20% but enemies by only 10%.
techniques.effectText: Sanative Rain restores 15% of all combatants on the battlefield's maximum HP.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its priority increases to Normal and instead restores 20% of allies maximum HP and restores 10% of rival's maximum HP.

techniques.name: 5PPEH
techniques.description: By striking the five vital points, the Miyako priests teach advanced tamers how to doom and immunize a target for 5 turns.
techniques.effectText: 5PPEH inflicts a single other target with a 5 turn countdown of the Doomed Condition but also gifts them with the Immune Condition for 5 turns.

techniques.name: Kesa Gatame
techniques.description: One of the best-known and most useful Miyako floor techniques, it pins down a target for SPD .
techniques.effectText: Kesa Gatame inflicts a single other target with SPD .

techniques.name: Lullaby
techniques.description: Twinkle twinkle little Tem / Whole opponent team falls Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Lullaby inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Unseen Blow
techniques.description: Nothing hurts like the blow you didn't see coming! This technique inflicts heavy damage.
techniques.effectText: Unseen Blow deals damage to a single other target.

gameDescription: Bigger and meaner than Shaolite, Shaolant have become the darlings of the tamers of Lochburg Dojo who want to command respect for their choice of squad.

name: Cycrox

techniques.name: Data Burst
techniques.description: Data input overflow! This sensory overload causes moderate damage.
techniques.effectText: Data Burst deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Strangle
techniques.description: Strangler and strangled, united in a deadly embrace. Both attacker and target get overextended next turn.
techniques.effectText: Strangle deals damage to a single other target but causes both the user and the target to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Tail Strike
techniques.description: Sweep the board at one fell swoop.
techniques.effectText: Tail Strike deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Toxic Slime
techniques.description: This takes the form of a repulsive wave of slime that hurts the body... and your self-esteem.
techniques.effectText: Toxic Slime deals damage to a single target.

techniques.name: Venomous Claws
techniques.description: When the look of your claws doesn't prevent the fight, the poison finishes it.
techniques.effectText: Venomous Claws deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Digithreat
techniques.description: Just like trash-posting, this technique is a slow way of inflicting damage to the mind...All those trash-posts are messing with your head... Used in combination with a Mental ally. Digithreat dooms the target for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Digithreat deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Mental ally, it also inflicts a 3 turn countdown of the Doomed Condition.

techniques.name: Meditation
techniques.description: Sync your breathing, become more aware of the space around you, feel your body and mind get Vigorized for 3 turns...
techniques.effectText: Meditation gifts the user with the Invigorated Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Slime
techniques.description: Nothing slows you down like being swamped in sticky goo... Traps for 2 turns and gives SPD .
techniques.effectText: Slime inflicts a single other target with SPD and the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Wastewater
techniques.description: Like raw sewage raining on you, without the "like". It inflicts moderate Toxic damage and poisons for 1 turn.
techniques.effectText: Wastewater deals damage to a single target and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 1 turn.

techniques.name: Venom Spread
techniques.description: This technique only works on already poisoned enemies - but in that case, the toxin rush inflicts 150 damage.
techniques.effectText: Venom Spread deals damage to a single target if they're afflicted with the Poisoned Condition.

techniques.name: Metabolize
techniques.description: This metabolic enhancement reacts to poison in the target's body by purging it and recovers 15% of health.Used in combination with a Nature ally, improved assimilation of nutrients regenerates the Temtem for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Metabolize cures a single other target of the Poisoned Condition and restores 15% of the user's maximum HP if the target was cured from the Poisoned Condition.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, it also gifts the user with the Regenerated Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Hologram
techniques.description: Let them attack your digital ghost while you evade them for 1 turn.
techniques.effectText: Hologram gifts the user with the Evading Condition for 1 turn.

techniques.name: Zen Meditation
techniques.description: Focus on your breathing. Remember, no effort, no resistance... The technique consumes 0 Stamina and boosts your ATK and SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Zen Meditation gifts the user with ATK and SPATK .

techniques.name: Harmful Microwaves
techniques.description: Make your enemies feel like reheated coffee does! This technique inflicts moderate damage.
techniques.effectText: Harmful Microwaves deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Digital ally, its STA Cost decreases to 14 and priority increases to High.

techniques.name: Restore
techniques.description: It's always good to have a backup... This quick technique restores 40% of the target's STA.Used in combination with a Water ally, Resotre also restores 20% STA to the user.
techniques.effectText: Restore restores 40% of a single other target's maximum STA.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also restores 20% of the user's maximum STA.

techniques.name: Paralyzing Poison
techniques.description: This strong venom traps and poisons the target for 4 turns.Used in combination with a Toxic ally, the poisoning lasts for 6 turns.
techniques.effectText: Paralyzing Poison inflicts a single other target with the Poisoned Condition for 4 turns and the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Toxic ally, the Poisoned Condition lasts 6 turns.

gameDescription: One rumor tells of a Mimit that fell into a Xolot. Another one, of a Nanto boffin accidentally spilling coffee on some circuitry. Be as it may, Cycrox is as close as it gets to a computer virus, but in the flesh... and in the silicon.

name: Hocus

techniques.name: Hypnosis
techniques.description: A brain hack developed by Arburian Mind specialists that makes the target Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Hypnosis inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Stare
techniques.description: This intimidating stare gives the Temtem Alert for 2 turns, and makes rivals feel more vulnerable: DEF .
techniques.effectText: Stare inflicts a single other target with DEF and gifts the user with the Alerted Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Beta Burst
techniques.description: A mighty beta-wave surge that bombards the target with a subatomic barrage.

techniques.synergyText: The following formula applies:

trivia: Hocus and its evolution are Lady Lottie's signature Temtem.

Despite Seismunch's Tempedia entry referring to it as an ape, Seismunch has a tail, which great apes do not have.
gameDescription: Seismunch are great apes, genetically close to humans and much more sophisticated than their lesser brethren. Highly imitative of human behavior, some are said to be nearing proto-human cognition.

techniques.effectText: Cage inflicts all combatants on the battlefield with the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Untangle
techniques.description: With a few swift movement, this techniques Untraps the target from any tangle. If trapped is removed successfully, the target gets DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Untangle cures a single target of the Trapped Condition and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF if they were cured from the Trapped Condition.

techniques.name: Purgation
techniques.description: Out with the bad, in with the good! This technique increases ATK and eliminates doomed.
techniques.effectText: Purgation gifts a single target with ATK and cures them of the Doomed Condition.

techniques.name: Rush
techniques.description: Hard or weak, what really matters is striking first. This superfast technique does exactly 40 damage but overextends the user for the next turn.
techniques.effectText: Rush deals an exact 40 damage to a single other target regardless of DEF, SPDEF, Type Effectivness, or Traits, but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Paralyzing Poison
techniques.description: This strong venom traps and poisons the target for 4 turns.Used in combination with a Toxic ally, the poisoning lasts for 6 turns.
techniques.effectText: Paralyzing Poison inflicts a single other target with the Poisoned Condition for 4 turns and the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Toxic ally, the Poisoned Condition lasts 6 turns.

techniques.name: Strangle
techniques.description: Strangler and strangled, united in a deadly embrace. Both attacker and target get overextended next turn.
techniques.effectText: Strangle deals damage to a single other target but causes both the user and the target to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Time Split
techniques.description: Twist the fabric of time-space to your advantage, gaining SPD and giving the enemy SPD .
techniques.effectText: Time Split deals damage to a single other target then gifts the user with SPD and inflicts the target with SPD .

gameDescription: Capable of communicating moods and intentions via complex patterns of its triple tail, these Temtem are aloof creatures who prefer the solitudes of the Arbury highlands. Although they mostly keep to themselves, their mindpower is formidable.

name: Momo

techniques.name: Nibble
techniques.description: Many Temtem have this habit of gently chewing plants and furniture. This is a little less gentle.
techniques.effectText: Nibble deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Bark
techniques.description: This Tem's bark is much worse than its bite - it gives the enemy DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Bark inflicts a single other target with DEF and SPDEF .

techniques.name: Head Charge
techniques.description: There are many clever uses for a large skull. This is not one of them, but it's effective.
techniques.effectText: Head Charge deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Brace
techniques.description: Survival is often the greatest of victories. Only effective if the Temtem is already alerted; removes it, gives evading for 2 turns and heals 10%.
techniques.effectText: Brace gifts the user with the Evading Condition for 2 turns and restores 10% of their maximum HP if they already have the Alerted Condition. The Alerted Condition is removed after.

techniques.name: Willpower Drain
techniques.description: Sapping the very will to fight from an enemy's mind, this quick Neutral technique steals 23 Stamina points.
techniques.effectText: Willpower Drain drains 23 STA from a single other target and restores 23 STA to the user. The user will still overexert if they don't have enough STA to use Willpower Drain. If the target has less than 23 STA, the user will only restore the amount that was drained.

techniques.name: Undermine
techniques.description: Leave your opponent heavily damaged and treading on very thin ice, giving it SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Undermine deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with SPATK .

techniques.name: Jaw Strike
techniques.description: Temtem with powerful jaws always know how to use them...
techniques.effectText: Jaw Strike deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Shelter
techniques.description: Take cover! This slow technique gives DEF and SPDEF at the expense of leaving you Overexerted on the next turn.
techniques.effectText: Shelter gifts the user with DEF and SPDEF but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Double Edge
techniques.description: Cuts both ways, in true Neutral fashion - inflicts moderate damage to the target, but also gives it DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Double Edge deals damage to a single other target and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its damage decreases to 1.

techniques.name: Zen Meditation
techniques.description: Focus on your breathing. Remember, no effort, no resistance... The technique consumes 0 Stamina and boosts your ATK and SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Zen Meditation gifts the user with ATK and SPATK .

techniques.name: Refresh
techniques.description: About time you took a little breather! This technique increases SPATK and heals 6% Health.
techniques.effectText: Refresh gifts the user with SPATK and heals 6% of their maximum HP.

techniques.name: Sanative Rain

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 20% of allies maximum HP Restore 10% of rival's maximum HP

techniques.description: Known as "the blessing rains of Kisiwa", this shamanic technique heals 15% of every Temtem on the battlefield..Used in combination with a Wind ally, Sanative Rain heals allied Temtem by 20% but enemies by only 10%.
techniques.effectText: Sanative Rain restores 15% of all combatants on the battlefield's maximum HP.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its priority increases to Normal and instead restores 20% of allies maximum HP and restores 10% of rival's maximum HP.

techniques.name: Restore
techniques.description: It's always good to have a backup... This quick technique restores 40% of the target's STA.Used in combination with a Water ally, Resotre also restores 20% STA to the user.
techniques.effectText: Restore restores 40% of a single other target's maximum STA.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also restores 20% of the user's maximum STA.

techniques.name: Knockback
techniques.description: What goes around comes around! This mighty attack inflicts massive damage, but the user gets 30% knockback damage.
techniques.effectText: Knockback deals damage to a single other target but causes the user to take 30% of the damage dealt as recoil.

trivia: Momo's cry resembles the "woof" barking sound of a dog.
This is the only known Temtem with heterochromia (having different iris colors).
Momo is a Breeder Tier Temtem by Kyle, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. He came up with the idea of a Siberian Husky-like Temtem and gave Crema complete freedom for the name and Luma coloration.
gameDescription: While some Temtemologist point to the primeval forests of Arbury and Cipanku as possible origin of this species, there is plenty of archaeological proof of their early domestication around Lake Moyo.

techniques.name: Pollution

gameDescription: Noxolotl are noble, dignified creatures. They are taken to exemplify the resilience and spirit of the Tucmani people, as "a beauty born of the foulest depths of Xolot, a light in the abyss", in the words of the poetess Itzia.

gameDescription: Blooze represent the opposite evolutionary path as compared to Toxolotl - blobby and bipedal, they are probably the oldest lifeform of Xolot, an atavic variety still largely unexplained by science.

Damage can be blocked if the target who would have taken damage has the Evading Condition, has the Electric Synthesize Trait, or, if the target is an ally, has the Friendship Trait.

The initial target takes 100% of the damage, the second takes 70%, and the third takes 60%. The chain of damage will fail to continue to the next target if the damage was blocked by the current target. Damage can be blocked if the target who would have taken damage has the Evading Condition, has the Electric Synthesize Trait, or, if the target is an ally, has the Friendship Trait.

techniques.name: Drill Impact
techniques.description: Nothing does armor piercing damage like a drill to the head.
techniques.effectText: Drill Impact deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Electric Storm
techniques.description: True Electric storm like the monsoon over Cipanku. Damages whole team.
techniques.effectText: Electric Storm deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.

techniques.name: Turbo Charge
techniques.description: Turn it to eleven! Decreases the Hold level of our whole team.
techniques.effectText: Turbo Charge decreases the Hold of all the techniques of a single team by 1.

techniques.name: Tornado
techniques.description: A powerful wind technique, illegal to use near all airship terminals of the Archipelago.
techniques.effectText: Tornado deals damage to a single target.

techniques.name: Blizzard
techniques.description: Cold and furious like the mistral winds in the Thalassian Cliffs.
techniques.effectText: Blizzard deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Turbo Choreography
techniques.description: The ancestral dance of Deniz is a powerful ritual that bestows protection, SPD to the whole team.Wind allies boost the effect of Turbo Choreography to the whole team SPD .

techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, it instead gifts SPD .

techniques.name: Misogi

techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also gifts the user with the Immune Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Noxious Bomb

techniques.effectText: Cage inflicts all combatants on the battlefield with the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.synergyText: If used with an Electric ally, its priority increases to High and also heals 10% of user's maximum HP.

trivia: Oceara appeared for the first time in the Mounts Kickstarter update, though little was known about it. Its official name and description were revealed on the official Temtem Twitter on 19/11/2018.
Oceara seems to be based off the Qilin/Kirin, antelopine divine creatures in Chinese and Japanese mythology respectively.

techniques.effectText: Frond Whip deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Soul Shout
techniques.description: A mighty scream, powered by the Temtem's very soul, inflicting considerable damage on an enemy.
techniques.effectText: Soul Shout deals damage to a single other target.

gameDescription: Probably the origin of old legends about dryads and forest trolls, this Temtem is a hulking quasi-arboreal of impressive strength and resilience. Like an oak, if oaks could punch.

name: Shuine

techniques.name: Nibble
techniques.description: Many Temtem have this habit of gently chewing plants and furniture. This is a little less gentle.
techniques.effectText: Nibble deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Glass Blade
techniques.description: Like death by a thousand cuts... but this is just one of them.
techniques.effectText: Glass Blade deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Aqua Bullet Hell
techniques.description: A devastating Water technique developed by legendary tamer Dan Maku.
techniques.effectText: Aqua Bullet Hell deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Iced Stalactite
techniques.description: Cold *does* bother you anyway... This giant icicle inflicts damage and also Cold for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Iced Stalactite deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Cold Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Flood
techniques.description: Watch the opponent get all bogged down. The whole team gets SPD .A mess of Mudshire proportions. Used in combination with an Earth ally, gives the enemy team SPD .
techniques.effectText: Flood inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with SPD .
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its STA Cost decreases to 22 and it instead inflicts SPD .

techniques.name: Crystal Bite
techniques.description: What do Crystal Temtem eat? Surely not other Temtem... but they can still take a vicious bite.
techniques.effectText: Crystal Bite deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Ninja Jutsu
techniques.description: The secret arts of the Cipanku shinobi! This technique lets you backstab enemies in the blink of an eye.
techniques.effectText: Ninja Jutsu deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Sacrifice
techniques.description: A Temtem may pay the ultimate price to heal the target of all Status conditions and give them DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Sacrifice removes/cures a single other target of all Status Conditions and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF , then the user is knocked-out.

techniques.name: Fluid Barrier
techniques.description: Real protection is not about unmovable strength, but dynamic defense. This technique gives the target immunity for 3 turns and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Fluid Barrier gifts a single target with SPDEF and the Immune Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Water Cannon
techniques.description: The strongest Sillaro current has nothing on this unstoppable jet.Used in combination with a Toxic ally, it produces a stream of Poison for 2 turns.

techniques.synergyText: If used with a Toxic ally, it also inflicts the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Antitoxins
techniques.description: Advanced antitoxins that cure poison on the inoculated target and invigorate them for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Antitoxins cures a single team of the Poisoned Condition and gifts them with the Invigorated Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Confiscate
techniques.description: Gimme all your stuff! The target is Seized for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Confiscate inflicts a single other target with the Seized Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Relax
techniques.description: Time for a little siesta! Everyone on the battlefield gets Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Relax inflicts all combatants on the battlefield with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Quartz Dirt
techniques.description: Micro-fine particles designed to inflict macro-damage to a whole team. Make sure you don't inhale them!A denser cloud. Used in combination with an Earth ally, Quartz Dirt traps the targets for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Quartz Dirt deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its damage increases to 80 and also inflicts the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Sanative Rain

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 20% of allies maximum HP Restore 10% of rival's maximum HP

techniques.description: Known as "the blessing rains of Kisiwa", this shamanic technique heals 15% of every Temtem on the battlefield..Used in combination with a Wind ally, Sanative Rain heals allied Temtem by 20% but enemies by only 10%.
techniques.effectText: Sanative Rain restores 15% of all combatants on the battlefield's maximum HP.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its priority increases to Normal and instead restores 20% of allies maximum HP and restores 10% of rival's maximum HP.

techniques.name: Restore
techniques.description: It's always good to have a backup... This quick technique restores 40% of the target's STA.Used in combination with a Water ally, Resotre also restores 20% STA to the user.
techniques.effectText: Restore restores 40% of a single other target's maximum STA.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also restores 20% of the user's maximum STA.

techniques.name: Mirror Shell
techniques.description: "Mirror, mirror in my hand, who's the best tamer in the Archipelago?" "No idea, but you get SPDEF ".
techniques.effectText: Mirror Shell gifts the user with SPDEF .

techniques.name: Quartz Shield
techniques.description: Temtem found defensive uses for rock crystal centuries before humans did: DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Quartz Shield gifts a single target with DEF and SPDEF .

trivia: Shuine is based on the feathered deities of Mesoamerican religions, with western dragon ears.
gameDescription: Colorful Shuine are a sight to behold, their bright scales reflecting Pansunlight as they frolic in the Kakama Cenote. They feed off the acidic components of Xolotic water, acting as natural filters and keeping cenote waters clean and fit for human consumption almost as effectively as the layers of volcanic rock.

name: Nessla

techniques.name: Bubbles
techniques.description: Bubbles! <3 This weakens the target by means of extreme cuteness.
techniques.effectText: Bubbles deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Water Blade
techniques.description: Whipping seawater, like the stormy Sillaro whipping the rocks.
techniques.effectText: Water Blade deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Chain Lightning
techniques.description: This miracle of Electric manipulation bounces 3 times clockwise for as long as it deals damage, dealing decreasing damage with each hit.
techniques.effectText: Chain Lightning deals damage to a single target then two other combatants in clockwise order from the initial target. The initial target takes 100% of the damage, the second takes 70%, and the third takes 60%. The chain of damage will fail to continue to the next target if the damage was blocked by the current target. Damage can be blocked if the target who would have taken damage has the Evading Condition, has the Electric Synthesize Trait, or, if the target is an ally, has the Friendship Trait.

techniques.name: Sparks
techniques.description: Nothing perks you up like a spark-up! SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Sparks gifts a single target with SPATK .

techniques.effectText: Strangle deals damage to a single other target but causes both the user and the target to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Tesla Prison
techniques.description: An electromagnetic trap that does light damage and slows down the target: SPD .

techniques.synergyText: Due to the low damage and high priority, its most encouraged use is to damage allies with the Asleep Condition in order to wake them.

techniques.name: Rend
techniques.description: While this technique does only moderate damage, it nullifies the target for 4 turns, buying you some precious time...
techniques.effectText: Rend deals damage to a single other target and gives them the Nullified Condition for 4 turns.

techniques.name: Laundry

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 10% of the user's maximum HP

techniques.description: Look, nobody likes doing laundry, but it has to be done, OK? It cleans all statuses, naturally! (And does some damage to boot.).
techniques.effectText: Laundry deals damage to a single target and cures/removes all of their Status Conditions.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Electric ally, its priority increases to High and also heals 10% of user's maximum HP.

techniques.name: Aquatic Whirlwind
techniques.description: This Water technique is faster than an angry Kalabyss.
techniques.effectText: Aquatic Whirlwind deals damage to a single target.

techniques.effectText: Bright Beam deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally and gifts the user with the Alerted Condition and Evading Condition for 2 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Crystal ally, its damage increases to 45.

trivia: Nessla was originally unnamed #33 on a list of scrapped Temtem that was to be voted to bring back on Kickstarter Update #2.
Nessla was one of the two winners of the Choose a Temtem backer mini-game during the Kickstarter.
gameDescription: Water and electricity are always a dangerous mix - and it's never as true as in the case of Nessla. These undulating, majestic creatures are at home in open waters, where their powerful electric discharges are most effective.

name: Valiar

techniques.description: Primal and instinctive, sometimes a good kick is all you need.
techniques.effectText: Kick deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.effectText: Bamboozle gifts a single target with the Evading Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Hypnosis
techniques.description: A brain hack developed by Arburian Mind specialists that makes the target Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Hypnosis inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.description: Use your head, non-metaphorically.
techniques.effectText: Head Ram deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, is priority increases to Normal and it also removes the target's Stat Stage Changes.

trivia: Valiar looks very different in its concept art compared to its final design. The main coloration is a dark and light purple, and Valiar is generally depicted with a stripe pattern instead of a spot pattern. In addition, some key details like the thick neck tuft are not present. The eyes have a completely different shape and color compared to the final version.
gameDescription: Although nobody has managed to decipher their language, the Valiar are assumed to be extremely intelligent. The Arburian dons are still trying to come up with a scientific explanation for the way Valiar use their expanding ears to boost their minds.

trivia: Pupoise is a Breeder Tier Temtem by Tutorxic, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. The design process for Pupoise and Loatle was shown on the "The Latest Breeder Tems and Route!" update on Crema's website.
Pupoise has a sticker on the official Temtem Discord, beating Halzhi by 71 votes, out of the total 237 votes, in the 3rd sticker poll.
gameDescription: Nature finds a way... particularly when Nature meets some of the most advanced circuitry. Pupoise are adaptive and are known to use simple tools and other innovations in the wild.

trivia: Loatle is a Breeder Tier Temtem by Tutorxic, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. The design process for Pupoise and Loatle was shown on the "The Latest Breeder Tems and Route!" update on Crema's website.
Loatle is one of four Temtem that change one of the types their pre-evolved form has upon evolving. In this case, swapping Nature for Mental. The others are Owlhe, Barnshe, and Waspeen.
Loatle is 1 of only 6 temtem with a sticker on the official Temtem Discord that didn't have to go through a sticker poll.
gameDescription: This Temtem straddles the twilight zone between natural and artificial intelligence, life and death... and the fact it resembles a dark creature from ancient lore doesn't help its reputation one bit...

techniques.effectText: Strangle deals damage to a single other target but causes both the user and the target to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Aqua Stone
techniques.description: "An ingenious application of hydraulic pressure for ballistic purposes" - Sophia d'Arissola.
techniques.effectText: Aqua Stone deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its damage increases to 104.

techniques.name: Toxic Ink
techniques.description: The victim will have time to regret getting this tattoo... While it's Poisoned for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Toxic Ink deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: High-pressure Water
techniques.description: An industrial-grade water jet that packs real punch.Used in combination with a Fire ally, it produced boiling water that inflicts Burn for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: High-pressure Water deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Fire ally, it also inflicts the Burned Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Humiliating Slap
techniques.description: A bruised ego hurts more than a wounded body. This is just the thing! DEF .
techniques.effectText: Humiliating Slap deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with DEF .

techniques.name: Flood
techniques.description: Watch the opponent get all bogged down. The whole team gets SPD .A mess of Mudshire proportions. Used in combination with an Earth ally, gives the enemy team SPD .
techniques.effectText: Flood inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with SPD .
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its STA Cost decreases to 22 and it instead inflicts SPD .

techniques.name: Waterjet
techniques.description: About time your enemies took a shower! This pressurized jet inflicts considerable damage and leaves the target Cold for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Waterjet deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Cold Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Rotten Goo
techniques.description: Eww, what's that stink? This gross, sticky mess damages the target and seizes it for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Rotten Goo deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Seized Condition for 2 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Electric ally, its priority increases to High.

techniques.name: Tsunami
techniques.description: Summon a rarely seen tidal wave that damages a whole team.Uses in combination with a Wind ally, damage boost and Cold for 3 Turns.
techniques.effectText: Tsunami deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its damage increases to 80 and also inflicts the Cold Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Wake Up
techniques.description: Wake up and smell the coffee! Inflicts minimal damage but wakes up the target instantly.
techniques.effectText: Wake Up deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: Due to the low damage and high priority, its most encouraged use is to damage allies with the Asleep Condition in order to wake them.

techniques.name: Major Slash
techniques.description: This blow targets the enemy's weak spot for massive damage.
techniques.effectText: Major Slash deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Laundry

synergyEffects.effect: Restore 10% of the user's maximum HP

techniques.description: Look, nobody likes doing laundry, but it has to be done, OK? It cleans all statuses, naturally! (And does some damage to boot.).
techniques.effectText: Laundry deals damage to a single target and cures/removes all of their Status Conditions.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Electric ally, its priority increases to High and also heals 10% of user's maximum HP.

techniques.name: Clinch
techniques.description: Give me a hug, bro! Ouch... but... not... like... thaaat...
techniques.effectText: Clinch deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Iced Stalactite
techniques.description: Cold *does* bother you anyway... This giant icicle inflicts damage and also Cold for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Iced Stalactite deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Cold Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Toxic Slime
techniques.description: This takes the form of a repulsive wave of slime that hurts the body... and your self-esteem.
techniques.effectText: Toxic Slime deals damage to a single target.

trivia: Kalabyss was revealed to the public on the official discord and the Kickstarter update #30.
gameDescription: How did Sillarian octopoda come in contact with mutagenic material is a matter of debate, but Kalabyss stand as an example of extreme adaption to the harshest environments - they have been known to survive a swim in Xolot Reservoir.

name: Adoroboros

techniques.name: Tail Strike
techniques.description: Sweep the board at one fell swoop.
techniques.effectText: Tail Strike deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Energy Manipulation
techniques.description: A simple yet quick Mental attack that exhausts the target for 1 turn.Used in combination with a Nature ally, Energy Manipulation does additional damage and exhausts for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Energy Manipulation deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Exhausted Condition for 1 turn.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, its damage increases to 60 and the Exhausted Condition lasts for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Toxic Ink
techniques.description: The victim will have time to regret getting this tattoo... While it's Poisoned for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Toxic Ink deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Psychic Collaborator
techniques.description: This Mental technique does a meagre 1 damage... It's all in your mind, after all.
techniques.effectText: Psychic Collaborator deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Mental ally, its damage increases to 170.

techniques.name: Beta Burst
techniques.description: A mighty beta-wave surge that bombards the target with a subatomic barrage.
techniques.effectText: Beta Burst deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Pollution
techniques.description: Noxious fumes, almost unheard-of in the unspoilt Archipelago. They Poison the whole team for 2 turns and also reduces 10% of stamina from the targets.
techniques.effectText: Pollution inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns and causes them to lose 10% of their maximum STA.

techniques.name: Lullaby
techniques.description: Twinkle twinkle little Tem / Whole opponent team falls Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Lullaby inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Sacrifice
techniques.description: A Temtem may pay the ultimate price to heal the target of all Status conditions and give them DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Sacrifice removes/cures a single other target of all Status Conditions and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF , then the user is knocked-out.

techniques.name: Toxic Gas
techniques.description: Hold your nose when you unleash this Toxic attack on the whole team.
techniques.effectText: Toxic Gas deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.

techniques.name: Denigrate
techniques.description: Sticks and stones... but this mental humiliation hurts too. It inflicts damage on the whole team.
techniques.effectText: Denigrate deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.

techniques.name: Wake Up
techniques.description: Wake up and smell the coffee! Inflicts minimal damage but wakes up the target instantly.
techniques.effectText: Wake Up deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: Due to the low damage and high priority, its most encouraged use is to damage allies with the Asleep Condition in order to wake them.

techniques.name: Misogi
techniques.description: The monks of Miyako developed this technique to eliminate all altered states on the Temtem.Using this waterfall meditation with a Water ally, you become immune for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Misogi cures/removes all Status Conditions gifted/given/inflicted on the user.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also gifts the user with the Immune Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Noxious Bomb
techniques.description: This nasty stinker inflicts Toxic damage... Just don't use it in an elevator...
techniques.effectText: Noxious Bomb deals damage to a single target.

techniques.name: Antitoxins
techniques.description: Advanced antitoxins that cure poison on the inoculated target and invigorate them for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Antitoxins cures a single team of the Poisoned Condition and gifts them with the Invigorated Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Confiscate
techniques.description: Gimme all your stuff! The target is Seized for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Confiscate inflicts a single other target with the Seized Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Relax
techniques.description: Time for a little siesta! Everyone on the battlefield gets Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Relax inflicts all combatants on the battlefield with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Horror
techniques.description: Unspeakable nightmares! Obviously, they can only hurt an asleep target, but they do massive damage to the sleeper.
techniques.effectText: Horror deals damage to a single target if they're afflicted with the Asleep Condition.

techniques.name: Held Anger
techniques.description: All that suppressed rage keeps building up... until it bursts in a nova of wrath.
techniques.effectText: Held Anger deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Hypnosis
techniques.description: A brain hack developed by Arburian Mind specialists that makes the target Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Hypnosis inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Inner Spirit
techniques.description: It is said this technique channels the spirit of a long-lost, draconic variety of Temtem, for massive damage.
techniques.effectText: Inner Spirit deals damage to a single target.

techniques.name: Virulent Gust
techniques.description: Don't you know that you're toxic? This technique does moderate damage.Can you feel me now? Used in combination with a Water ally, Virulent Gust inflcits damage on the whole enemy team.
techniques.effectText: Virulent Gust deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Water ally, its targeting changes to Other Team or Ally. As such, if the user targets themselves and the synergy activates, only the user's ally will be damaged.

trivia: Adoroboros was originally shown on the Choose-a-Temtem V3 poll, currently unnamed. It got second place with 554 votes, just 25 votes behind the winner.
Adoroboros's name was voted on in the Naming Contest for #129. The final name won by just 13 votes out of the total 823 votes.
gameDescription: Few Temtem are as deceptive as Adoroboros - an unusual mix of cute and deadly, combining the most sophisticated Mental tricks with the basest Toxic traits. They are a fine example of the incredible natural diversity of the Archipelago.

name: Tuwai

trivia: Pigepic's design is likely based on the English phrase, "when pigs fly", which is used to describe an impossible situation.
Despite being Temtem number #141, Pigepic was the first Temtem to be revealed to the public via Twitter.
Pigepic has 2 emotes on the official Temtem discord.

The Temtem Discord community created "cults" worshiping Saku and Pigepic. The official Twitter account for Temtem later created a tweet pitting the “Sakult” and “Team Porket” against each other. The Sakult is currently the winner.

trivia: Given the Iridescence Trait and the Mental subspecies, Koish is the only Temtem that is weak to Neutral attacks.
Given the Iridescence Trait and either the Mental, Digital, or Melee subspecies, Koish is the only Temtem that is resistant to Digital attacks.

Koish has 2 possible whisker lengths, 2 possible fin sizes, 6 possible colors for each of its 3 tail stripes, and 12 type combinations (each with a different pool of tail colors). This results in 864 variations of each Koish type and 10,368 variations total, not including Lumas.
Koish, along with Chromeon, are the only Temtem with a subspecies for each type.
gameDescription: Unique amongst all Temtem, Koish sub-species are known to span all Temtem types. This extreme range of diversity is attributed to early mutations in the Xolotic-Moyoan-Sillarin ocean of prehistoric Paninsula.

techniques.description: Healing is a collective process - in clockwise order, 3 Temtem recover 20% health.
techniques.effectText: Chain Heal restores 20% of a single target's and two other combatant's maximum HP in clockwise order from the initial target. When only two combatants are on the battlefield, the initial target will restore 40% while the remaining target will restore 20%.

techniques.name: Bush

techniques.effectText: Bush gifts the user with the Regenerated Condition and Evading Condition for 1 turn.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, it also gifts the user with SPDEF .

techniques.name: Plague

techniques.name: Dust Vortex

techniques.effectText: Dust Vortex deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Jinxed Whisper

techniques.effectText: Jinxed Whisper inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Brace
techniques.description: Survival is often the greatest of victories. Only effective if the Temtem is already alerted; removes it, gives evading for 2 turns and heals 10%.

techniques.name: Look out
techniques.description: This Temtem has (metaphorical) eyes on the back of its head. This hyperalert state makes it alerted for 5 turns and removes the Asleep status condition.
techniques.effectText: Look out gifts a single target with the Alerted Condition for 5 turns and cures them of the Asleep Condition. Unlike other techniques, it will set the duration of any previously gifted Alerted Conditions to 5 turns.

techniques.name: Quicksand
techniques.description: Can we all sink any lower? Every Temtem on the battlefield gets SPD .Used in combination with a Wind ally, only the enemy team gets SPD .
techniques.effectText: Quicksand inflicts all combatants on the battlefield with SPD .
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, it only affects the rival team.

techniques.name: Sludge Gift
techniques.description: An extremely weak Earth technique... but you don't look a sludge gift in the rock, right?
techniques.effectText: Sludge Gift deals damage to a single other target.

gameDescription: Extremely perceptive and aware, this species flourishes (in all senses of the word) in the great expanses of wild land - although they are inquisitive by nature, and never shy away from human contact.

techniques.name: Hologram
