name: Minothor

techniques.name: Nibble
techniques.description: Many Temtem have this habit of gently chewing plants and furniture. This is a little less gentle.
techniques.effectText: Nibble deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Tenderness
techniques.description: Really? Are you going to attack something *this* cute? Inflicts ATK .
techniques.effectText: Tenderness inflicts a single other target with ATK .

techniques.name: Energy Manipulation
techniques.description: A simple yet quick Mental attack that exhausts the target for 1 turn.Used in combination with a Nature ally, Energy Manipulation does additional damage and exhausts for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Energy Manipulation deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Exhausted Condition for 1 turn.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, its damage increases to 60 and the Exhausted Condition lasts for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Kick
techniques.description: Primal and instinctive, sometimes a good kick is all you need.
techniques.effectText: Kick deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Double Kick
techniques.description: An effective and cool-looking double kick inspired by Cipanki action movies.
techniques.effectText: Double Kick deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Sparkling Bullet
techniques.description: All flash and no bang - this sparkly Electric technique does little damage.
techniques.effectText: Sparkling Bullet deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its damage increases to 105.

techniques.name: Stampede
techniques.description: A stampede worth of the Kisiwan savanna. Damages the whole team.Used in combination with an Earth ally, inflicts extra damage and seizes for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Stampede deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its damage increases to 125 and also inflicts the Seized Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Head Ram
techniques.description: Use your head, non-metaphorically.
techniques.effectText: Head Ram deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Piezoelectric Blow
techniques.description: This Temtem can compress a part of its body to unleash an electric shock - fast and damaging.Oh, and you have an earthing electrode? Used in combination with an Earth ally, Piezoelectric Blow inflicts additional damage and seizes for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Piezoelectric Blow deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its damage increases to 155 and also inflicts the Seized Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Hasty Lunge
techniques.description: An all-out attack, no time or thought for defense! It's fast, inflicts moderate damage but also overextends the user during their next turn.Used in combination with a ally, Hasty Lunge doesn't overextend the user.
techniques.effectText: Hasty Lunge deals damage to a single other target but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, it won't overexert the user.

techniques.name: Blackhole
techniques.description: Gravity in the Middle Sphere is capricious and mild - but this technique still causes a great deal of damage and wipes all statuses from the target.Used in combination with an Earth ally, Blackhole also wipes all stage changes.
techniques.effectText: Blackhole deals damage to a single target and cures/removes their Status Conditions.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, is priority increases to Normal and it also removes the target's Stat Stage Changes.

techniques.name: Madness Buff
techniques.description: There is an edge to this madness - those willing to take 30% Damage will get SPDEF and SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Madness Buff causes the user to lose 30% of their maximum HP and then is gifted SPATK and SPDEF .

techniques.name: Purgation
techniques.description: Out with the bad, in with the good! This technique increases ATK and eliminates doomed.
techniques.effectText: Purgation gifts a single target with ATK and cures them of the Doomed Condition.

techniques.name: Thunder Strike
techniques.description: Hear it roar! The sound and fury of this technique inflict heavy damage but Exhaust the attacker for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Thunder Strike deals damage to a single target but inflicts the user with the Exhausted Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Turbo Charge
techniques.description: Turn it to eleven! Decreases the Hold level of our whole team.
techniques.effectText: Turbo Charge decreases the Hold of all the techniques of a single team by 1.

techniques.name: Ultrasound
techniques.description: If you can hear it, you've already been hit. This hyper-fast technique exhausts the whole target team for 1 turn.
techniques.effectText: Ultrasound inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Exhausted Condition for 1 turn.

gameDescription: Some of the oldest cave paintings in the Chini Grotto are said to represent prehistorical Minothor. Its ability to transform Mental power into electricity and vice versa must have looked like magic to early humans...

name: Maoala

techniques.name: Novice Punch
techniques.description: Just one step above a slap, but everybody's got to start somewhere.Used in combination with a Melee ally, it changes the technique type to Melee and becomes a more powerful punch.
techniques.effectText: Novice Punch deals damage to a single other target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Melee ally, it becomes Melee Type and its damage increases to 51.

techniques.name: Meditation
techniques.description: Sync your breathing, become more aware of the space around you, feel your body and mind get Vigorized for 3 turns...
techniques.effectText: Meditation gifts the user with the Invigorated Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Paralyzing Poison
techniques.description: This strong venom traps and poisons the target for 4 turns.Used in combination with a Toxic ally, the poisoning lasts for 6 turns.
techniques.effectText: Paralyzing Poison inflicts a single other target with the Poisoned Condition for 4 turns and the Trapped Condition for 2 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Toxic ally, the Poisoned Condition lasts 6 turns.

techniques.name: Jinxed Whisper
techniques.description: Shh! Shut up, you're jinxing your chances! The target falls asleep for 2 turns, but the user gets overextended on the next turn.
techniques.effectText: Jinxed Whisper inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Hypnosis
techniques.description: A brain hack developed by Arburian Mind specialists that makes the target Asleep for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Hypnosis inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Telekinetic Shrapnel
techniques.description: Reportedly feels "like combing your brain with concertina wire."
techniques.effectText: Telekinetic Shrapnel deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Double Gash
techniques.description: "'Tis but a scratch! Or two!". This Melee Technique is nothing to write home about.
techniques.effectText: Double Gash deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Nito Seiho
techniques.description: Derived from Cipanki martial traditions, this technique deals a powerful Melee strike and gives them DEF .
techniques.effectText: Nito Seiho deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with DEF .

techniques.name: Blackhole
techniques.description: Gravity in the Middle Sphere is capricious and mild - but this technique still causes a great deal of damage and wipes all statuses from the target.Used in combination with an Earth ally, Blackhole also wipes all stage changes.
techniques.effectText: Blackhole deals damage to a single target and cures/removes their Status Conditions.
techniques.synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, is priority increases to Normal and it also removes the target's Stat Stage Changes.

techniques.name: Depress
techniques.description: Aren't we all? Just take another nap. This technique inflicts exactly 120 damage without waking up the target.
techniques.effectText: Depress deals an exact 120 damage to a single other target, regardless of DEF, SPDEF, Type Effectivness, or Traits. It will also not cause a target afflicted with the Asleep Condition to wake up.

techniques.name: Wake Up
techniques.description: Wake up and smell the coffee! Inflicts minimal damage but wakes up the target instantly.
techniques.effectText: Wake Up deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: Due to the low damage and high priority, its most encouraged use is to damage allies with the Asleep Condition in order to wake them.

techniques.name: Zen Meditation
techniques.description: Focus on your breathing. Remember, no effort, no resistance... The technique consumes 0 Stamina and boosts your ATK and SPATK .
techniques.effectText: Zen Meditation gifts the user with ATK and SPATK .

techniques.name: Rush
techniques.description: Hard or weak, what really matters is striking first. This superfast technique does exactly 40 damage but overextends the user for the next turn.
techniques.effectText: Rush deals an exact 40 damage to a single other target regardless of DEF, SPDEF, Type Effectivness, or Traits, but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Haito Uchi
techniques.description: A slashing open-hand strike in the Cipanki martial arts tradition. Inflicts Physical damage and leaves them Asleep the same turn.
techniques.effectText: Haito Uchi deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Asleep Condition for 1 turn.

gameDescription: A favorite of Lochburgian tamers, Maoala are companionable Temtem, always up for a fun party or a hearty battle, equally at home in the dojo and in the pub.

name: Venx

techniques.name: Scratch
techniques.description: Almost any claw or nail can scratch the surface. Sometimes that's enough.
techniques.effectText: Scratch deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Heavy Blow
techniques.description: Effective and unsubtle, like a Tucmani mine drill.
techniques.effectText: Heavy Blow deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Strangle
techniques.description: Strangler and strangled, united in a deadly embrace. Both attacker and target get overextended next turn.
techniques.effectText: Strangle deals damage to a single other target but causes both the user and the target to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Shelter
techniques.description: Take cover! This slow technique gives DEF and SPDEF at the expense of leaving you Overexerted on the next turn.
techniques.effectText: Shelter gifts the user with DEF and SPDEF but causes the user to be overexerted the next turn.

techniques.name: Head Ram
techniques.description: Use your head, non-metaphorically.
techniques.effectText: Head Ram deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Savage Suplex
techniques.description: In classic Temtem wresting showbiz style, this Neutral technique damages and exhausts the target for 2 turns.
techniques.effectText: Savage Suplex deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Exhausted Condition for 2 turns.

techniques.name: Late Torment
techniques.description: The first cut is the deepest, but the last one hurts like Downbelow. This Neutral Technique only works on trapped enemies and inflicts 180 damage.
techniques.effectText: Late Torment deals damage to a single other target if they're afflicted with the Trapped Condition.

techniques.name: Sacrifice
techniques.description: A Temtem may pay the ultimate price to heal the target of all Status conditions and give them DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Sacrifice removes/cures a single other target of all Status Conditions and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF , then the user is knocked-out.

techniques.name: Unseen Blow
techniques.description: Nothing hurts like the blow you didn't see coming! This technique inflicts heavy damage.
techniques.effectText: Unseen Blow deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Base Jump
techniques.description: It's not the jump that hurts, it's the landing - and it hurts the target A LOT.
techniques.effectText: Base Jump deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Brace
techniques.description: Survival is often the greatest of victories. Only effective if the Temtem is already alerted; removes it, gives evading for 2 turns and heals 10%.
techniques.effectText: Brace gifts the user with the Evading Condition for 2 turns and restores 10% of their maximum HP if they already have the Alerted Condition. The Alerted Condition is removed after.

techniques.name: Untangle
techniques.description: With a few swift movement, this techniques Untraps the target from any tangle. If trapped is removed successfully, the target gets DEF and SPDEF .
techniques.effectText: Untangle cures a single target of the Trapped Condition and gifts them with DEF and SPDEF if they were cured from the Trapped Condition.

techniques.name: Ninja Jutsu
techniques.description: The secret arts of the Cipanku shinobi! This technique lets you backstab enemies in the blink of an eye.
techniques.effectText: Ninja Jutsu deals damage to a single other target.

trivia: Venx is one of only three Temtem lines that can evolve into multiple different Temtem. The other two are Towly and Tuwai.

Venx is the only Temtem that evolves into one of two Temtem depending on its trait.
Since the trait that Venx requires to have to evolve is kept, the player must use a Telomere Hack - Trait Swap (or a Telomere Hotfix - Trait Swap if its a Luma) after evolving to get Venmet's or Vental's other Trait.

techniques.description: Sticks and stones... but this mental humiliation hurts too. It inflicts damage on the whole team.

techniques.name: Horror
techniques.description: Unspeakable nightmares! Obviously, they can only hurt an asleep target, but they do massive damage to the sleeper.
techniques.effectText: Horror deals damage to a single target if they're afflicted with the Asleep Condition.

techniques.description: The secret arts of the Cipanku shinobi! This technique lets you backstab enemies in the blink of an eye.

gameDescription: Lady Cathrine of Properton herself popularized this species among the fashionable tamers of her age. Nowadays, it is considered one of the timeless classics of Arburian Temtem breeds.

name: Chimurian

techniques.name: Peck
techniques.description: All beaked Temtems like to playfully peck their tamers. This is the less friendly version.
techniques.effectText: Peck deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Glass Blade
techniques.description: Like death by a thousand cuts... but this is just one of them.
techniques.effectText: Glass Blade deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Sharp Leaf
techniques.description: Evolution has armed Nature Temtem with advanced defenses against herbivores.
techniques.effectText: Sharp Leaf deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Rage
techniques.description: The red mist makes a Temtem brutal but also careless, getting ATK and DEF .
techniques.effectText: Rage gifts the user with ATK but also inflicts them with DEF .

techniques.name: Gaia
techniques.description: Invoke the ancient spirit of the Omninesian jungle to recover 100% STA and 20% of the user's max HP.
techniques.effectText: Gaia restores 20% of the user's maximum HP and 100% of their maximum STA. The user will still overexert if they lack the required STA before use.

techniques.name: Multiple Pecks
techniques.description: A rapid-fire flurry of furious beaks.
techniques.effectText: Multiple Pecks deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Burrow
techniques.description: "In a hole in the ground there lived a Temtem..." which allowed it to evade for 4 turns.
techniques.effectText: Burrow gifts the user with the Evading Condition for 4 turns.

techniques.name: Sharpening
techniques.description: Sharpen those claws, it's time to tear through the opposition! This technique bestows increased ATK and SPD .
techniques.effectText: Sharpening gifts the user with SPD and ATK .

techniques.name: Frond Whip
techniques.description: Feel the true force of Nature, unleashed as a savage lash of the whip!
techniques.effectText: Frond Whip deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Crystal Plume Gatling
techniques.description: What's more damaging than a feather gatling? Well, a * Crystal shard* gatling! Worse than a broken mirror!
techniques.effectText: Crystal Plume Gatling deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Confiscate
techniques.description: Gimme all your stuff! The target is Seized for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Confiscate inflicts a single other target with the Seized Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Footwork
techniques.description: Advanced balance training developed by Tucmani rockhoppers: it confers SPD .
techniques.effectText: Footwork gifts the user with SPD .

techniques.name: Look out
techniques.description: This Temtem has (metaphorical) eyes on the back of its head. This hyperalert state makes it alerted for 5 turns and removes the Asleep status condition.
techniques.effectText: Look out gifts a single target with the Alerted Condition for 5 turns and cures them of the Asleep Condition. Unlike other techniques, it will set the duration of any previously gifted Alerted Conditions to 5 turns.

techniques.name: Mirror Shell
techniques.description: "Mirror, mirror in my hand, who's the best tamer in the Archipelago?" "No idea, but you get SPDEF ".
techniques.effectText: Mirror Shell gifts the user with SPDEF .

gameDescription: Some urban legends claim this variety wasn't tamed or bred as much as extracted from mineral ores in the deepest pits of Quetzal. Just how its roots interface with the crystals of its body is still a subject of scientific study.

name: Arachnyte

techniques.name: Nibble
techniques.description: Many Temtem have this habit of gently chewing plants and furniture. This is a little less gentle.
techniques.effectText: Nibble deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Jaw Strike
techniques.description: Temtem with powerful jaws always know how to use them...
techniques.effectText: Jaw Strike deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Token
techniques.description: Launch token attacks, get token results. This technique does little damage.
techniques.effectText: Token deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Willpower Drain
techniques.description: Sapping the very will to fight from an enemy's mind, this quick Neutral technique steals 23 Stamina points.
techniques.effectText: Willpower Drain drains 23 STA from a single other target and restores 23 STA to the user. The user will still overexert if they don't have enough STA to use Willpower Drain. If the target has less than 23 STA, the user will only restore the amount that was drained.

techniques.name: Cozy Net
techniques.description: Arachnyte are adept weavers, and their webs look so temptingly soft... This technique traps a target and makes it fall asleep for 3 turns.Used in combination with a Nature ally, Cozy net also regenerates the user for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Cozy Net inflicts a single other target with the Asleep Condition and the Trapped Condition for 3 turns.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, it also gifts the user with the Regenerated Condition for 3 turns.

techniques.name: Venom Spread
techniques.description: This technique only works on already poisoned enemies - but in that case, the toxin rush inflicts 150 damage.
techniques.effectText: Venom Spread deals damage to a single target if they're afflicted with the Poisoned Condition.

techniques.name: Plague
techniques.description: A nasty lurgy that damages the target and leaves it Exhausted for 1 turn.
techniques.effectText: Plague deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Exhausted Condition for 1 turn.

techniques.name: Unseen Blow
techniques.description: Nothing hurts like the blow you didn't see coming! This technique inflicts heavy damage.
techniques.effectText: Unseen Blow deals damage to a single other target.

techniques.name: Execution
techniques.description: "Omnes vulnerant, postuma necat". Slowly the hour creeps onwards... it does only slight damage, but if that leaves the Temtem under 35% of their total HP... it's over for them.
techniques.effectText: Execution deals damage to a single other target and if this damage would put them below 35% of their maximum HP, they're instead instantly knocked-out.

techniques.name: Digithreat
techniques.description: Just like trash-posting, this technique is a slow way of inflicting damage to the mind...All those trash-posts are messing with your head... Used in combination with a Mental ally. Digithreat dooms the target for 3 turns.
techniques.effectText: Digithreat deals damage to a single target.
techniques.synergyText: If used with a Mental ally, it also inflicts a 3 turn countdown of the Doomed Condition.

techniques.name: Knockback
techniques.description: What goes around comes around! This mighty attack inflicts massive damage, but the user gets 30% knockback damage.
techniques.effectText: Knockback deals damage to a single other target but causes the user to take 30% of the damage dealt as recoil.

techniques.name: Awful Song

gameDescription: In Cipanki lore, dragons are born of lightning to roam the vast reaches of heaven. Sometimes, a curious member of their race will visit the Archipelago and befriend a human. They are never considered "tamed" - they merely consent to accompanying a tamer for a few years or even decades.
